 <body>
  <div id="tplPage" class="wspUi"><div id="tplTitle"><div id="tplTitleLogo"><img src="../res/logoOpale3.png" alt width="48" height="48"></div><span id="tplTitleMain">Opale</span><span id="tplTitlesub">&quot;Academic&quot; pedagogical content creation</span></div><div id="tplTabs"><div id="tplTabCo"><div id="tplTabCoScroll"><div class="infoblock"><h1 class="infoblock_ti">Module</h1><div class="infoblock_co"><div class="text "><p class="txt_p ">An Opale <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/module_icon.png" alt width="17" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Module</code> can contain two types of activities:</p><ul class="txt_sl "><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/activite_apprentissage_icon.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Learning activity</code> (source of knowledge),</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/activite_eval_icon.png" alt width="19" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Self-assessment activities</code> (mastered skills validation).</span></li></ul><p class="txt_p ">These activities can be grouped in <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/division_icon.png" alt width="17" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Divisions</code>.</p><p class="txt_p ">The module is linked to the different media to be published: <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/supportWeb.png" alt width="18" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Web</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/supportPapier.png" alt width="18" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Print</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/supportDiapo.png" alt width="18" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Slideshow</code>.</p></div></div></div><div class="infoblock"><h1 class="infoblock_ti">Learning activity</h1><div class="infoblock_co"><div class="text "><p class="txt_p ">A <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/activite_apprentissage_icon.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Learning activity</code> is composed of:</p><ul class="txt_sl "><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/grain_contenu_icon.png" alt width="12" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Content elements</code> to present and structure information;</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span> <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/exo_redac_icon.png" alt width="16" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Writing task</code>, practical activity with Contextualization - Question - Solution;</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span>Interactive pedagogical activities (see quizzes list below);</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/questSynth.png" alt width="15" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Comprehensive questions</code>, optional, at the end of the activity, to encourage the learner to rephrase what he learned.</span></li></ul><p class="txt_p ">The goal of a learning activity is to <strong class="txt_emphasis_is ">provide knowledge while having the learner actively engage in the learning process</strong>.</p><p class="txt_p ">The type of information delivered in your course is explicitly specified by  <cite class="txt_alt_is ">pedagogical blocks</cite> (<code class="txt_term_tl ">Information</code>, <code class="txt_term_tl ">Warning</code>, <code class="txt_term_tl ">Reminder</code>, <code class="txt_term_tl ">Fundamental</code>, <code class="txt_term_tl ">Example</code>,...).</p><p class="txt_p ">Into a <code class="txt_term_tl ">Content element</code>, the information can be grouped into as many titled <code class="txt_term_tl ">Parts</code> as you like.</p></div></div></div><div class="infoblock"><h1 class="infoblock_ti">Self-assessment activity</h1><div class="infoblock_co"><div class="text "><p class="txt_p ">A <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/activite_eval_icon.png" alt width="19" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Self-assessment activity</code> is composed of quizzes:</p><ul class="txt_sl "><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/qcu.png" alt width="14" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Single choice question</code> (Textual or <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/qcuGraph.png" alt width="23" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Graphical</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/qcm.png" alt width="15" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Multiple choice question</code> (Textual or <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/qcmGraph.png" alt width="23" height="17"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Graphical</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/categ.png" alt width="17" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Matching</code>and <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/ordo.png" alt width="16" height="11"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Jumble words</code> exercises with words or images to drag and drop,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/tat.png" alt width="17" height="11"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Fill-in the gaps</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/questionF.png" alt width="13" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Short answer question</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/questionNum.png" alt width="15" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Numerical answer question</code>.</span></li></ul><p class="txt_p ">Quizzes can be grouped into  <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/listeExo.png" alt width="15" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Quizzes lists</code>.</p><p class="txt_p ">The goal of a self-assessment activity is to <strong class="txt_emphasis_is ">validate knowledge acquisition with a wide range of interactive quizzes</strong>.</p></div></div></div><div class="infoblock"><h1 class="infoblock_ti">References</h1><div class="infoblock_co"><div class="text "><p class="txt_p "><span class="txt_vName_el ">Opale</span> allows the creation of various reference items:</p><ul class="txt_sl "><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/abreviation_icon.png" alt width="15" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Abbreviation</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/glossaire_icon.png" alt width="16" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Glossary</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/bibliographie_icon.png" alt width="17" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Bibliography</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/reference_icon.png" alt width="19" height="16"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Reference</code>.</span></li></ul><p class="txt_p "> These items are designed for content re-purposing: use several times, in  your set of training modules, a piece of information you wrote once.</p><p class="txt_p ">Reference items are linked in the editorial content and offer the reader a piece of extra information (in a pop-up in web media or with a reference to an index in a paper-based document).</p></div></div></div><div class="infoblock"><h1 class="infoblock_ti">Resources</h1><div class="infoblock_co"><div class="text "><p class="txt_p "><span class="txt_vName_el ">Opale</span> allows you to insert various multimedia resources into your content, namely:</p><ul class="txt_sl "><li class="txt_m "><span> images (<span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/png.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">png</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/jpg.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">jpg</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/gif.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">gif</code>) and <code class="txt_term_tl ">images galleries</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span> videos ( <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/mp4.png" alt width="23" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">mp4</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/webm.png" alt width="23" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">WebM</code>,...) and subtitling files ( <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/srt.png" alt width="18" height="12"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">srt</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/webvtt.png" alt width="19" height="12"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">WebVTT</code>),</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span>audio files (<span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/mp3.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">mp3</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/mp3.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Ogg</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/son-opus_icon.png" alt width="25" height="18"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">opus</code>),</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/flash.png" alt width="21" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Flash animations</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/ods.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">ods tables</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span> <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/odg.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">odg graphs</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span> mathematical formulae (<span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/odf.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">odf equations</code> and  <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/latex.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span>  <code class="txt_term_tl ">LaTeX</code>),</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span>usual office documents (<span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/doc.png" alt width="21" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Word</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/xls.png" alt width="21" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Excel</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/ppt.png" alt width="21" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">PowerPoint</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/odt.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">odt text</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/odp.png" alt width="21" height="15"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">odp slideshow</code>,   <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/pdf.png" alt width="21" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">pdf</code>, <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/zip.png" alt width="21" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">zip</code>),</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/listingInfo.png" alt width="22" height="17"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Source code</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span> <span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/siteWebEmb.png" alt width="23" height="14"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Embedded websites</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/moduleWebDist.png" alt width="23" height="17"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Remote web modules</code>,</span></li><li class="txt_m "><span><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/ico_appletJava_icon.png" alt width="25" height="19"></span> <code class="txt_term_tl ">Java applets</code>.</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="note block"><h1 class="note_ti block_ti"><span class="block_ti_co"><span class="blockTitle">Filter mechanism</span></span></h1><div class="note_co block_co"><div class="text "><p class="txt_p "> Filters enable excluding parts of content from a document when publishing it. One can generate two versions of the same module using <span class="txt_vName_el ">Opale</span>:</p><ul class="txt_il "><li class="txt_ili "><p class="txt_p "><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/ico_filtreVL.png" alt width="18" height="18"></span> <strong class="txt_emphasis_is ">Standard version</strong></p></li><li class="txt_ili "><p class="txt_p "><span class="txt_ico_tim "><img src="../res/ico_filtreVC.png" alt width="20" height="15"></span>  <strong class="txt_emphasis_is ">Short version</strong></p></li></ul><p class="txt_p ">A piece of content is automatically excluded from a version when the corresponding filter icon is checked. One  chooses which version to publish while configuring the publication item. The content &quot;filtered&quot; from the version is automatically excluded during the document generation.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div id="tplTabBar"><a href="presentation.html" target="_self" class=" tabSel_no"><span>Presentation</span></a><span class=" tabSel_yes"><span>Quick help</span></span><a href="nvtes.html" target="_self" class=" tabSel_no"><span>New features</span></a><a href="Opale_Advanced.html" target="_self" class=" tabSel_no"><span>About...</span></a></div></div></div>
